<a id="introduction"></a>
<h4>Introduction</h4>

Ordering Management System, OMS in the future, was developed to handle ordering of car models by different categories of clients including retailers and distributors. While ordering is done exclusively by clients, that is users that have 'client' role assigned to them, system itself is managed by 2 privileged roles: "stff" and "administrator".
This section of the help file describes functionality available to staff members (see <%= link_to "User Categories", "#user_categories" %> below) 

<p>&nbsp;</p>
<a id="ordering"></a>
<h4>Ordering</h4>

Ordering is done by registered clients. 
There are two ways to order products: directly from product list, by entering number for each selected product, or by goling to Orders page and clicking on <Add Product To Cart> button at the bottom. In both cases, entered number of selected product will be added to shopping cart, which whill show as a shopping cart symbol and number in upper right corner of the page. Once selection is finished and all products are added to shopping cart, you can finalize the order by first clicking on shopping cart symbol which will open shopping cart modal, where you can either submit order or empty shopping cart and start from the beginning. 

<p>
Once order is submitted several things will happen: 

<ul>
<li> - Inventory is updated: number of available products is automatically reduced by the ordered number </li>
<li> - Emails are sent: Order confirmation email to the user, Order notification to staff members and  Low quantity notification to staff if number of available products is nevative </li>
<li> - PO and Invoice for the new order are generated and order is assigned 'Pending' status </li>
</ul>


